      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a 5-year property class, the MACRS depreciation formula is:\n\nDepreciation = (Cost - Residual Value) / (Year of Acquisition x MACR)\n\nWhere MACR is the Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System rate for the year.\n\nThe half-year convention assumes that the asset is placed in service on July 1st of the year of acquisition, and the first half-year of depreciation is calculated as follows:\n\nHalf-year Depreciation = (Cost - Residual Value) / 2\n\nFor a 5-year property class, the MACR rates are:\n\n* Year 1: 20%\n* Year 2: 32%\n* Year 3: 19.2%\n* Year 4: 11.52%\n* Year 5: 7.2%\n\nYou can use these rates to calculate the annual depreciation, and then apply the half-year convention to calculate the half-year depreciation.\n\nFor example, if the cost of the equipment is $100,000 and the residual value is $20,000, the annual depreciation for Year 1 would be:\n\nDepreciation = ($100,000 - $20,000) / (1 x 0.20) = $80,000",
      "source": "target",
